def report_rf_size(layers_per_stack, n_stacks, sample_rate, kernel_size):
    secs = wn.receptive_field_size(total_layers=layers_per_stack * n_stacks,
                                   num_cycles=n_stacks,
                                   kernel_size=kernel_size) / sample_rate
    print('%f seconds' % secs)
    
print('Old receptive field size:')
report_rf_size(layers_per_stack=10, n_stacks=3, sample_rate=22050, kernel_size=3)
print('New receptive field size:')
report_rf_size(layers_per_stack=10, n_stacks=6, sample_rate=16000, kernel_size=5)

Old receptive field size:
0.278413 seconds
New receptive field size:
1.534563 seconds

SR = 16000

def play_examples(name, training_secs, dir_path):
    display(HTML('<h2>%s</h2>' % name))
    display(HTML('<h3>%.2f hours of training</h3>' % (training_secs / 3600)))
    for filename in os.listdir(dir_path):
        path = os.path.join(dir_path, filename)
        display(Audio(data=np.load(path), rate=SR))
        
def play_training_set(name, dir_path):
    filenames = os.listdir(dir_path)
    display(HTML('<h2>%s training set (%d examples)</h2>' % (name, len(filenames))))
    for filename in filenames:
        path = os.path.join(dir_path, filename)
        display(Audio(np.load(path), rate=SR))
        
def show_loss_curve(path):
    steps = []
    losses = []
    for line in open(path).readlines():
        step, loss = line[:-1].split(',')
        steps.append(int(step))
        losses.append(float(loss))
        
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    fig.suptitle('Training loss vs batch')
    ax.set_xlabel('Batch')
    ax.set_ylabel('Loss')
    ax.plot(steps, losses)
    plt.show()

def get_training_secs(path):
    return time() - float(open(path).read())

play_examples('Generated audio from WaveNet overfitted on Nsynth',  9 * 3600, 'nsynth-overfitting-examples')
play_training_set('Nsynth', 'nsynth-overfitting-training-set')
show_loss_curve('nsynth-overfitting-loss-curves/batch-train_no_dev.txt')
